# Lychee URL exclusions for the markdown-links CI job.
# Each entry is a Rust regex matched against the full URL. Add a one-line
# comment above the entry explaining why it is excluded. See Issue #10.

# nestjs-zod GitHub repo: the package author's handle has rotated; the
# `risenforces/nestjs-zod` URL cited in ADR-0002 (EN+RU narrative+design,
# 4 occurrences) returns 404. The npm registry (https://www.npmjs.com/
# package/nestjs-zod) is the stable, content-addressed reference; the
# GitHub URL is kept inline for historical context but lychee ignores it.
^https://github\.com/risenforces/nestjs-zod($|/.*$)

# Org-level Projects v2 boards under doctor-school: project boards are
# private, so lychee (unauthenticated) gets 404 even when the project
# exists. The URL is useful for owner / agent navigation; verified
# manually rather than by CI. DSP-198 board #1 is the current example.
^https://github\.com/orgs/doctor-school/projects/.*$

# npmjs.com scoped-package pages: the registry returns 403 Forbidden to
# lychee's unauthenticated user-agent for scoped packages (e.g.
# @stoplight/spectral-owasp-ruleset, cited in the endpoint-authz-matrix
# design spec). The page exists and is content-addressed; verified
# manually. Same false-positive class as the nestjs-zod entry above.
^https://www\.npmjs\.com/package/@stoplight/spectral-owasp-ruleset($|/.*$)

# Imported Claude Design source (design-source/): reference material, not a
# runnable app. (1) The provenance links in its README point at the login-gated
# Claude Design canvas, which unauthenticated lychee cannot reach. (2) The
# imported design-system.dc.html references the canvas-side runtime + logo assets
# (support.js, assets/ds-logo-*.svg) that we intentionally do NOT vendor (see the
# folder README). Both are verified manually / re-pullable via DesignSync — same
# false-positive class as the private Projects v2 boards above.
^https://claude\.ai/design/.*$
design-source/assets/
design-source/support\.js

# Lint-guard test fixtures deliberately carry placeholder/broken markdown links
# (e.g. a MEMORY.md fixture mimicking the auto-memory index). They are test data,
# not docs — exclude the whole fixture tree from the link check. See #293.
tools/lint/guard-tests/fixtures/
